commit.message:
Add proper exit value for signals, per spec

* Also adds optional key timeout for job outputs

Merge pull request #2 from daroczig/create_outputs_without_unlock_args

Skip extending unlock_outputs arg as it might no be available at all
jobs.py: error: argument --unlock-outputs: not allowed with argument --create-outputs
Fixes command-line and jobs version for install

Fixed --upstream, --downstream to get all edges

* --depth 0 is now sane relative to depths 1+

Many more command-line options

* --depth (depth limit)
* --before (timestamp, datetime, date limited)
* --after (timestamp, datetime, date limited)
* And some untestested job start functionality (for using jobs.py fully as
  a script, for simple command-line integration with *any* system that can
  call out to a scipt)
Fix for imports, testing, and fallthrough
Fixed makefile, cleaned up edge upstream/downstream display
Actual initial commit of the library, docs, etc.
